"{\"uid\": \"ms.now-top-stories-latest-simone-biles-olympics-gold-2024-gymnastics-vance-rcna164462\", \"text\": \"Opinion  Morning Joe  RacheL Maddow  Deadline: White House  The weekend  NEWSLETTERS  Share this -  Biles wrote, \\\"lack of talent, lazy, olympic champions,\\\" alongside photos of her and her teammates on the floor, ecstatic at their win.  Three years ago, whenSimone Bileswithdrew from the U.S. women's gymnastics team final at the Tokyo Olympicsto focus on her mental health, she faced a barrage of criticism,including from right-wing punditswho called her \\\"weak\\\" and \\\"selfish.\\\"  On Tuesday,Biles led Team USA to a triumphant gold medalafter they scored a nearly six-point winover their competitors.  In an Instagram post later in the day, Biles appeared to respond to critics, writing \\\"lack of talent, lazy, olympic champions\\\" alongside photos of her and her teammates Sunisa Lee, Jordan Chiles, Jade Carey and Hezly Rivera celebrating their win on the floor.  Biles' caption appeared to be a pointed reference to her former teammate Mykayla Skinner's comments last month. In a now-deleted YouTube video, Skinner - who replaced Biles in the 2020 team final after she withdrew - criticized the team, saying \\\"a lot of girls do not work as hard.\\\"  \\\"Besides Simone, I feel like the talent and the depth just is not like what it used to be,\\\" Skinner said. \\\"The girls just do not have the work ethic.\\\"RecommendedKnow Your ValueSimone Biles, Diane Von Furstenberg, Sophia Bush, and more to headline Know Your Value, Forbes' 30/50 SummitKnow Your Value staffLatestN.J. Gov.-elect Mikie Sherrill tells Democrats: 'Move quickly and actively, not passively'Allison DetzelShe later posted astatementapologizing for her comments.The team's gold medal Tuesday was a victorious comeback after winning silver in the last Olympics. Several of the Team USA gymnasts had overcome significant mental and physical health issues in recent years: Bilespublicly struggled with the \\\"twisties,\\\"which led to her stepping down from the last Olympics' team final; Lee, who won the Olympic all-around title in Tokyo, wasdiagnosed with two kidney diseaseslast year; and Chiles, who hasgrappled with the expectations in gymnastics, had considered letting go of the sport.Biles' withdrawal from the Tokyo team final, in particular, drew intense criticism from conservatives, many of whom jumped on the opportunity toturn her into a culture war villaindespite showing no understanding of the rigorous demands of professional sports. Turning Point USA founderCharlie Kirkcalled her a \\\"selfish sociopath,\\\" North Carolina Lt. Gov.Mark Robinsonsaid she was \\\"weak,\\\" and JD Vance, who was running for the Senate at the time and is now Donald Trump's running mate,questionedwhy people were praising Biles for putting her mental health first.Biles, 27, became the most decorated gymnast in U.S. history with her team's gold medal Tuesday. So far, no word from her critics on that.  She later posted astatementapologizing for her comments.  The team's gold medal Tuesday was a victorious comeback after winning silver in the last Olympics. Several of the Team USA gymnasts had overcome significant mental and physical health issues in recent years: Bilespublicly struggled with the \\\"twisties,\\\"which led to her stepping down from the last Olympics' team final; Lee, who won the Olympic all-around title in Tokyo, wasdiagnosed with two kidney diseaseslast year; and Chiles, who hasgrappled with the expectations in gymnastics, had considered letting go of the sport.  Biles' withdrawal from the Tokyo team final, in particular, drew intense criticism from conservatives, many of whom jumped on the opportunity toturn her into a culture war villaindespite showing no understanding of the rigorous demands of professional sports. Turning Point USA founderCharlie Kirkcalled her a \\\"selfish sociopath,\\\" North Carolina Lt. Gov.Mark Robinsonsaid she was \\\"weak,\\\" and JD Vance, who was running for the Senate at the time and is now Donald Trump's running mate,questionedwhy people were praising Biles for putting her mental health first.  Biles, 27, became the most decorated gymnast in U.S. history with her team's gold medal Tuesday. So far, no word from her critics on that.  Clarissa-Jan Lim    Clarissa-Jan Lim is a breaking news reporter for MS NOW. She was previously a senior reporter and editor at BuzzFeed News.  Latest Post  \\u00a9\\u00a02026 Versant Media, LLC\"}"